Distribution Statistics

Source: R/stats-chisquare-tbl.R
util_chisquare_stats_tbl.Rd

Returns distribution statistics in a tibble.

util_chisquare_stats_tbl(.data)

Arguments

.data

The data being passed from a tidy_ distribution function.

Value

A tibble

Details

This function will take in a tibble and returns the statistics of the given type of tidy_ distribution. It is required that data be passed from a tidy_ distribution function.

See also

Other Chisquare: tidy_chisquare()

Other Distribution Statistics: util_beta_stats_tbl(), util_binomial_stats_tbl(), util_cauchy_stats_tbl(), util_exponential_stats_tbl(), util_f_stats_tbl(), util_gamma_stats_tbl(), util_geometric_stats_tbl(), util_hypergeometric_stats_tbl(), util_logistic_stats_tbl(), util_lognormal_stats_tbl(), util_negative_binomial_stats_tbl(), util_normal_stats_tbl(), util_pareto_stats_tbl(), util_poisson_stats_tbl(), util_t_stats_tbl(), util_uniform_stats_tbl(), util_weibull_stats_tbl()

Author

Steven P. Sanderson II, MPH

tidy_chisquare() %>%
  util_chisquare_stats_tbl()
